Robert Myron


1941 - 2017
Obituary
Condolences

Flowers

































 MYRON, Robert W. "Bob" Age 76 of Fairfield, formerly of Pittsburgh, PA passed away July 19, 2017 in Cincinnati. He was born June 17, 1941 in Pittsburgh, PA the son of Charles and Mercedes (Didion) Myron. On June 5, 1965, Bob married Vicki Greco in Monessen, PA. They later moved to the Cincinnati area in 1971, where he worked for Mosler Safe Co. for over 30 years, and several other companies, until semi-retiring a few years ago. Bob was very active in community affairs: President of BCMH Board; Fairfield Park and Recreation; Fairfield City Council; and the Community Arts Advisory Committee. He loved his sports, especially the Cincinnati Bengals and College sports. Bob leaves his loving wife of over 52 years, Vicki Myron; son, Patrick (Julia) Myron; daughter, Kelly (David) Ash; and 3 grandchildren, Isis, Jude, and Vincent Ash. He was preceded in death by his parents; brother, Charles Myron; and several cousins in the Greater Pittsburgh Area. Visitation will be 9:30-10:30 a.m., Monday, July 24, 2017 at the Avance Funeral Home & Crematory, 4976 Winton Rd., Fairfield, OH 45014. Mass of Christian Burial will follow, 11 a.m., Monday at the Sacred Heart Catholic Church, 400 Nilles Rd., Fairfield with Father Larry Tharp, Celebrant. Memorials may be made to The  or the . The family will accept condolences at www.avancefuneralhome.com



Published in Dayton Daily News on July 23, 2017


